<h4>Department Description</h4>
<p>In a world where information is more readily available from more sources and more rapidly disseminated than ever before, the ability to communicate correctly, clearly, precisely and persuasively has never been more important.</p>
<p>We believe all future Communication professionals should develope a solid, broad foundation of knowledge and skills. Students should be able to write and speak confidently and well to a wide range of audiences; to research and analyze scenarios and develop sound ideas and solutions; to get along and work with diverse people in many kinds of situations; to serve in groups constructively or lead them productively; and to produce targeted, effective, written, spoken and visual messages in media, group and interpersonal settings.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
